This paper deals with the capacity of mobile ad hoc networks (MANETs) to deliver multicast messages within a given delay constraint. The paper focuses on the impact of network size, number of multicast sessions, and mobility model on the multicast capacity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses information theory tools to analyze the multicast capacity, which makes cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper proposes a joint coding/scheduling algorithm to achieve the multicast capacity, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also studies the impact of mobility models on the multicast capacity, which is related to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
